21/11/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Serbian President Boris Tadic and his Montenegrin counterpart Filip Vujanovic told a joint press conference in Podgorica on Friday (November 19th) that their countries have achieved significant results in their joint efforts to fight organised crime in light of a recent extradition agreement.
The two leaders expressed mutual support for their EU bids.
Vujanovic said he is confident in Serbia's sincere efforts to achieve full co-operation with The Hague war crimes tribunal by apprehending the two remaining war crimes fugitives -- Ratko Mladic and Goran Hadzic.
(Vecernje Novosti - 20/11/10;
Tanjug, Beta, B92, Emportal - 19/11/10)
